title: Franchise value of the Oakland Raiders ( NFL ) 2002 to 2019
yAxis: Franchise value in million U.S. dollars
summary: The chart at hand is a line chart where the x axis denotes Year and a y axis denotes Franchise value in million U.S. dollars. In total the number of data points it has is 18.
Overall Franchise value in million U.S. dollars has increased over the Year.
The most drastic increase took place within the Year 2015 and 2016.
The highest Franchise value in million U.S. dollars, of value 2900.0 was reached at Year 2019
The lowest Franchise value in million U.S. dollars, of value 421.0 was reported at Year 2002
